Events.Text: <i>The house lights rose slightly, casting a soft glow about the crowd.░ Above us, a familiar voice came over the PA.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Thank you all for coming to the evening showing of the 50's classic movie, "The Amazonian Queen".
Events.Title: Cryptic

Events.Text: <i>Even in the dim light, I could see Dustin's face plastered with a grin.░ His hand brushed over mine for a moment, giving it a gentle squeeze as he beamed an excited smile in my direction.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Accompanying the movie will be our house organist, to better preserve the same experience as the movie's release.
Events.Title: Cryptic

Events.Text: Because of this, we ask that you turn off all cell phones and other electronic devices.░ For your safety, be aware of the exits to either side of the screen in the case of emergency.
Events.Title: Cryptic

Events.Text: Now relax and enjoy one of the early cinematic classics: The Amazonian Queen!
Events.Title: Cryptic

Events.Text: <i>A flurry of clapping rose from the audience as the house lights dimmed once more.░ As the film started up on the screen, the dull glow of a phone and some scattered snickering drew my attention to the row in front of us.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Of course once the organ began to echo through the theater, my eyes snapped to the flickering screen ahead.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>The movie opened on a man sitting on a dock by the river, a small riverboat bobbing the in the water nearby.░ The shadow of a figure passes over him and a woman in far more elegant dress stands behind him.
Dustin leaned in to whisper in my ear.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>That's Daisy Smith. She's a missonary in South America and she was seperated from the rest of the group when they discovered plans to attack a major military base held by the good guys.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: No spoilers, Dustin.░ I want to enjoy the movie as it is.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Despite him pretty much explaining what's on the screen already, it's kind of fun to hear him tell me about it.░ That and it gives me an excuse to get closer to him.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Once the woman has secured passage on the boat, and the man is unaware she carries important information for the Allied forces, the two of them find they are extremely incompatable.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>As the journey goes on, the two of them begin to rub each other the wrong way more frequently.░ He's snapping at her and she's hiding away in the cramped cabin, trying desperately to keep her courage up.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Now, he's specifically in the jungle to try to stay out of the conflict.░ He lost his father to the previous war and hid away in the Amazon to avoid the draft, so he doesn't want any part of what she's doing.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>The snickering from the teenagers in front us spiked at the sight of the woman falling face first into the dirty cot she's been given to sleep on.░ Dustin's eyes narrowed at the distraction.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Just ignore them, Dustin.░It's not worth runing the movie.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Hey you kids! Shut up, we're watching a movie here!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>One of them looked back at me, sneering for a moment before turning back to their friends.░ They did quiet down, though.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: As time passes, the two of them begin to enter a part of the jungle that's under the control of the bad guys.░ Avoiding gunfire, shells and attempts to board the small boat, the man loses the woman when she is captured by enemy forces.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Alone on the boat, the man is just about to leave the checkpoint when we see him ball a fist and sock the guard right in the face.░ He heads deeper into the jungle, to the bad guy's bunker and waits in the pouring rain for a chance to slip inside.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>This is the part where he realizes that staying neutral was just letting the other side win.░ Losing Daisy was like losing his father all over again and he realizes he has to do something!
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>It's at that point that the teens burst into laughter. Met with a few shushes from the other theater goers nearby, they simply mock them back and keep laughing.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: You kids either shut up or I'll throw you out myself!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Two of them turn back, glowering at me for a moment before they see Dustin's expression.░ At the sight of the perturbed lion, they sink back into their seats and grow quiet.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I tried to ignore them, cuddling up more with Dustin, when a fortunate explosion on screen managed to quiet them enough to pay attention to the movie again.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Setting the bunker's ammo piles on fire provides enough of a distraction for the two of them to escape.░ As they rush back to the boat, she notices the blood on the side of his shirt and looks up to see his pained face.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Feeling Dustin tense up, I look up at him to see him biting his lip.░ He really wants to talk about this movie.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I smiled up at him, squeezing his arm and shaking my head.░ He sighed and nodded, wrapping his arm over my shoulder and giving me a squeeze in return.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Alright, alright. I give. Spoiler away.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>A look of relief came over his face as he gave my cheek a nuzzle in thanks.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Back on the boat, she tends to his wounds.░ It's touch and go for a while as she learns to run the ship while keeping him in bed.░ Necessity keeps them civil, but as time passes, they find it easier and easier.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Saving her gave him some small closure for not being old enough to save his father and she sees that the rough and tumble man really does have a heart of gold.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>With only moments left to reach the command base before the attack, the two of them do everything they can to lighten the load and speed up the ship.░ We watch as she throws her luggage overboard, leaving the tattered dress she wears as her only posession.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>They finally reach the command post, rushing in past the guards to relay the information in the nick of time.░ The commander sends his men out to arrest the traitors and guard the perimeter.░ In the mean time, the two of them collapse in the medical tent, thier hands falling into each others before they sleep.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I love this part. Her sacrifice only further confirms his feelings towards her.░ He couldn't be bothered to get involved when the world was on fire around him but her determination is enough to draw him out of that shell and drive him to action.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>The teenagers are at it again, making kissy noises and laughing uproariously.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Leaning over the seat in front of me, I smack one of the kids upside the head.░ Startled, he jumps up, turning back with a balled fist to see half the theater, me and Dustin included, giving them all the death stare.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>After a moment of hushed whispers, the teenagers shuffle defeated and grumpy out of the theater.░ The guy behind me pats me on the shoulder as Dustin beams at me.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>As I feel Dustin start to stand, I squeeze his arm and shake my head.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Just ignore them, the movie is almost over. Don't let them ruin it.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Begrudingly, he settled back into his seat.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>With the conflict won in the region, the woman begs the man not to return to the river.░ He is hesitant, but a kiss on the cheek from the woman draws him close. The two of them embrace and with a final passionate kiss, the movie comes to a close.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Applause rolled through the theater, many people standing up in their seats.░ Dustin and I worked our way through the crowd and back out into the lobby.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>The lobby is bustling as people chat about the movie, plans for afterward and just stretch after being in the theater seating for so long.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: So? What did you think of the movie?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: It was amazing!░ I mean, I can see what you mean about it crafting the cliches but you could tell it was authentic by where it was coming from.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: It was a good movie, but nothing I hadn't seen before.░ I'm certainly glad I came out to see it, though.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: To be honest, it was kinda a snooze-fest for me.░ I guess I'm just more of a modern movie goer.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I know! I mean it's cliche now but back then, they were really playing with the medium.░ It was all new and amazing back then!
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: It's an acquired taste, I'll admit.░ Glad you weren't bored though. It was also good to see it with someone else. Nothing sadder for me than going to a movie by myself.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Fighting, torture, chases, escapes and true love...░ and you call it a snoozefest. <i>Heh...
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Thanks for not spoiling the movie for me.░ I like to go into these things fresh.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Man, it was hard not to.░ I absolutely love to talk about movies and that one in particular,░ but we've all got our comfort zones and I respect that... usually.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I thought I didn't want you to spoiler it for me, but that dialogue really added some more depth to the movie for me.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Thanks for indulging me.░ I love talking about movies and that one in particular.░ There's just so many more layers to it than you think possible.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: ...and can I say, nice job dealing with the teens.░ Watching them skulk out of there. It was priceless.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Those twerps needed to shut up, movie or not.░ People came here to relax and be entertained, not deal with someone else's kids.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: It just sucks that those kids kept acting up.░ It ruined the movie for me.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I just didn't see the point of making a scene.░ They clearly weren't about to stop regardless.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Believe me, I could have gotten 'em to shut up.░ I can be very persuasive.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: No doubt there.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Nothing gets people to quiet down faster than a big, burly lion only inches away from them.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>To emphasize the point, he stood a hair's breadth away from me.░ I could feel the warmth radiating off of him and my knees weakened a little.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Pleased with my reaction, he stepped back enough to give me some breathing room and ran a paw through his mane.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Maybe.░ Still, sometimes ya gotta stand up for yourself.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Standing there in silence for a moment, I finally piped up.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I had a good time, Dustin.░ Did you want to grab some proper food or maybe take a walk?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I think...░ we should head back to my place.░ We could have a couple of drinks and maybe get to know each other better in a more intimate setting.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text:
I think...░ this isn't going to work out.░
You're cute, kid, but I just got out of something serious and I think I rushed in to this.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>It was nearly ten in the evening and I still had plenty of things to do tomorrow.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I should probably get going.░ It was nice to get out though.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Hang on there, kid.░ I didn't say I was done with you tonight.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I think a better idea would be to stop in by my place and relax for the night.░ We could have a couple of drinks, chat for a while...░ I'm sure nothing you've got going on tomorrow is more important than that.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Probably best.░ Guess there really wasn't anything there.░ Have a good night, kid. Maybe I'll see ya if you need a cup of coffee.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Dustin gave me a half wave and strolled out of the lobby, leaving me standing there.░ I guess the date didn't go as well as I thought it did.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>As I walked home, I began to wonder what all went wrong.░ Maybe Dustin was right and there just wasn't anything there.░ I've still got his number, I could give him a call if I wanted.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Coby wasn't back yet from where he'd gone tonight and sitting alone in a dark room didn't seem a very productive use of my time.░ Unless I wanted to collapse into bed.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: What?░ I thought things were going well.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Look, kid...░ It's sweet and all, but you're just not what I'm looking for. Better we gave it a shot and realized this before it got bad.░ Maybe I'll see you if you grab some coffee.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Standing there agasp, I watched him give me a quick little wave before heading out the front door.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Feeling completely alone in a crowd of people, it was all I could do to keep it together.░ Was I just that bad at dating?░ Or was he right, and there wasn't anything there in the first place?░ I still had his number, I suppose I could call if I still wanted to work this out.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>In the meantime, I should probably head home. It's getting late.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>The walk home was pretty uneventful. I kept going over the date in my mind, thinking about what he said and what I should do next.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Stumbling into the bedroom, I slumped down on the edge of my bed.░ Coby still wasn't back from whatever his plans were tonight; leaving me with my phone and my bed as my only real options.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I could feel a smile ticking the edges of my mouth as I strode up closer to him.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Sounds like a great idea.░ Lead the way!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Guess the date went better than I thought, and what harm could come from a couple of drinks?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I guess you're right.░ Besides, it's a nice night for a walk.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>What does he mean by done with me?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Before I could seriously respond, he stepped up close to me again, those stong arms slipping down to my hips.░ I couldn't hold back the gasp as those claws pricked me lightly through my clothes.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: So...░ Let's just take a little stroll back to my place and see where the night takes us.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Block after block, the trip back to his place kept my cheeks permanently flushed.░ Dustin's paws wouldn't keep to themselves and my weak attempts to struggle away were only met with him drawing me in closer.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: C'mon, kid.░ I know you like this. I could see it in the club and at the theater.░ You want a big strong guy to take charge.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>I stammered weakly, whimpering as I felt that broad paw caressing the small of my back.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I like it too.░ Getting to control someone, make them do whatever I want.░The fact that you're cute too just sweetens the deal.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>I kept glancing around, making sure no one saw me blushing up a storm and desperately trying to hide my growing arousal.░ For his part, it just pushed him further.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Heh.░ Already gettin' a little tight down there, kid?░ You're just bursting at the seams, aren't you?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Despite the awkwardness of how I was forced to walk with the urgency in my groin, I did manage to make it into both his building and his elevator before he got more aggressive.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>The doors had barely closed when I felt his warm breath on my neck, one paw trailing up along my inner thigh.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: It's the eagerness that makes it fun, kid.░ The fact that you can't control yourself around me. That turns me on something fierce.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>We almost spilled out of the elevator, my whole body tingling as Dustin guided me with a paw on my backside to his door.░ He slid the key in with one hand, pushing open the door and pulling me in afterwards.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Neither of us thought to turn on the lights. Instead, he leaned in close and pressed his lips against my mouth, clutching me as we kissed.░ His paws groped me even more forcefully as I ground my body against him.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>When the lights suddenly came on, Dustin pinning me back against a wall as he lifted my leg up against his hip, the two of us glanced about in surprise.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Sitting on the leather couch in the middle of the living room was a familiar parrot.░ It was the one I saw back at the club!░ To my chagrin, Dustin released me, leaving me slumped against the wall as he turned to face that smug snarl on the bird's beak.
Events.Title: %playername%

Choices.Text: I'm not exclusively a sub, you know?
Fair enough, I guess you have me pegged.

Events.Text: Do you want me to get my hands off then?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Cool, fine. No subby shit.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Heh.░ Already gettin' a little tight down there, kid?░ Gonna melt the elastic, or what?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Guess it didn't take long for you to find someone else, huh?
Events.Title: Vareoth

Events.Text: You're one to talk, Var. Particularly when you send me a picture of you getting railed by three other guys!░ What the hell are you doing breaking into my apartment?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text:
First,░ I didn't break in. I still had a key.
Second,░ it's my father's watch I lent you. I need it back.
Events.Title: Vareoth

Events.Text: Lent me? You gave it to me for our first anniversary and didn't say anything about it belonging to your dad!░ What the fuck, Var?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I still need it back.░ He's been looking for it and he'll have my hide if he thinks I lost it.░ It's not like you ever wore it anyway.
Events.Title: Vareoth

Events.Text: Hrnnn...░ Just... just wait right here, Var. I'll get your damn watch and I boxed up your stuff already.░ You can take it all, leave my key and get out.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Pfft.░ Fine. No down off my ass. Then you can get back to diddling your little fucktoy here, I suppose.
Events.Title: Vareoth

Events.Text: <i>Dustin stepped into the bedroom, his eyes narrowed and his nostrils flaring.░ This guy knew all too well how to get under his fur.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: So you're the latest conquest, huh?░ Saw you talking to him at the club.
Events.Title: Vareoth

Events.Text: <i>Despite wanting to say something, I kept my mouth shut. I didn't want to get Dustin into any more trouble and this guy definately wasn't worth it.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Really?░ So on top of cheating, sleeping around and making a public nusance of yourself, I can add spying to the list?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Lion got your tongue?░ Haha,░ smartest move you could make. I've got Dustin wrapped around my finger.░ You might think you've got something but I can get him back in a moment if I wanted.
Events.Title: Vareoth

Events.Text: <i>I took a short breath, just looking in the direction of the bedroom door and trying to tune him out.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: You think this is the first time we've had a blow up like this?░ Last time, the sex was mind-blowing. He fucked me so hard I couldn't walk for a week.░ Just stayed here in his bed while he pampered me and then plowed me every night.
Events.Title: Vareoth

Events.Text: <i>It was getting considerably more difficult to ignore the parrot's smirking face.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: So it doesn't matter what you think you've got.░ He's just going to drop you off on the curb the instant you bore him.
Events.Title: Vareoth

Events.Text: <i> I turned back to him, my fingers tensing as Dustin walked back into the room.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Alright, Var. Here's your shit and that watch.░ Now, there's the door. See yourself out and leave the key.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>With one last smirk in my direction, the parrot set the key dramatically on the coffee table and grabbed his box.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Have fun you two.░ Don't do anything I wouldn't do.
Events.Title: Vareoth

Events.Text: <i>Dustin slammed the door behind his ex and slumped against it.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Sorry about that.░ That guy is a force of nature. Can't believe we stayed together for so long.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Got a mouth on you too.░ Probably why he's going out with you. He likes people to badmouth me when we're on a break.
Events.Title: Vareoth

Events.Text:
Wait. What?░
What's that supposed to mean?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>He laughed heartily and made a dismissive wave in my direction.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: You really think this is the first time we fought?░ Last time I got to throw a vase around, smash a few things up.░ He's a hot-blooded guy; he needs excitement and nothing gets the blood pumping like a fight.
Events.Title: Vareoth

Events.Text: You're kidding me. You provoke him just to get him mad?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Sometimes I do it just to spice things up when they're getting too routine.░ The make-up sex is amazing. For two weeks after our last breakup, we fucked three times a day every day.
Events.Title: Vareoth

Events.Text: You're full of it.░ Being an emotionally manipulative asshole for sex doesn't work.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Oh?░ Did you have some experience with that? Maybe I should let Dustin know so he can get you out of the way faster.░ Doesn't matter though, we always make up and we always get back together.
Events.Title: Vareoth

Events.Text: Looks pretty final to me right now.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: That just shows what you know.░ Don't worry, he'll dump you by the curb when I come back and apologize.░ He'll give me his house key again, we'll ruin his sheets and you can go back to your desperate little life alone.
Events.Title: Vareoth

Events.Text: <i>My hand had curled into a first when Dustin walked back into the room.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Running into Dustin's ex, even if it was the first official time, had been far from a pleasant experience.░ From Dustin's sagging shoulder and distant look, I could tell it was rough on him too.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I didn't mean for this to happen for a second time,░ but maybe we should end the night here.░ Arguing with Var about his bullshit was always a major mood killer even when we were dating.
Events.Title: Dustin

Choices.Text: So this is going to be a problem?

Events.Text: I didn't sign up for this to have someone else able to crash this at a moment's notice.░ The guy's a jerk and letting him have this effect on you is playing right into his hands.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Look, kid.░ The last thing I need right now is you trying to pull some guilt trip on me. Var's an asshole but we had our good times. You can't just turn that off like a switch.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: But he's manipulating you!░ He pretty much admitted it to me while you were upstairs!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Tact, kid.░ It's actually a thing and you need to start exercising some of it.░ Var's been a part of my life for a long time and getting untangled from that isn't so simple.░ You can either be patient and let me deal with it or you can walk now.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: You know that's not what I meant, Dustin.░ I just hate to see him taking advantage of what you used to have to ruin what we could have.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I can see that,░ but 'us' is still in the planning stages here.░ I know I'm eager to get in a little fun here and there but that's only because I like you as well.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: What does all that mean, then?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Tonight, it means we wind up with blue balls 'cause life likes to throw curves.░ Next time you're free, though, give me a call.░ I do want to stick through this.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Var's still a problem, I'm sure but Dustin's been nothing but honest with me.░ Maybe a little patience is all that's called for.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Fair enough,░ but I want that second date. Expect a call in the near future.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Hah,░ seriously,░ I'll be eagerly waiting, %playername%
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Dustin leaned in slowly and pressed his lips gently against my cheek, wrapping me up in those muscled arms.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I'll be expecting that phone call.░ For now, I'm gonna collapse into bed.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>As much as I wanted to follow after him, I turned back towards the door.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>No one said dating was going to be simple, and going out with Dustin certainly proves that point.░ Still, we had some fun times tonight. I really hope we can take this somewhere.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Now, I just have to figure out what I'm going to do with the rest of my night.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Then I guess this is where I leave.░ I didn't get into dating to be someone's rebound from their crazy ex,░ and I certainly don't want to go through being dumped in the end either.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Well, then...░ there's the door kid. Don't let it hit you on the ass on the way out.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Standing there, fuming to myself, I wanted to yell at him. To shout into that somber face that this was just the further proof I needed to know this was going nowhere.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Instead, I just left. Shut the door behind me and walked down the hall.░ No point in trying to salavge something if it just meant that his ex was going to waltz in a screw it all up.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I still didn't know why he couldn't see it, since it was plain as day.░ Didn't matter now though. Likely he wouldn't consider anything further now anyway.░ Nothing to do but head home.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Of course it wasn't that late and no one else was home.░ I suppose I could always go back out or call someone else and see what they were up to.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I get it. It's complicated when you've been with someone for so long, even if they do turn out to be a jerk.░ Seen it happen to my brother, had it happen to me before.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Thanks %playername%.░ I don't like it any better than you, but...░ Oof... Just talking about it is exhausting.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I can go.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Dustin walked from the living room to the doorway where I was, gathering me up in his arms and pressing his lips to mine in a tender kiss.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I hope you believe me when I say, this is the last thing I wanted to have happen.░ I had a great time tonight and I want to see you again.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I want to see you too.░ Let's just end on this and we'll save up for the next time.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I'm just glad you said there's going to be a next time.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Of course.░ I'm not a single date kinda guy.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>We kissed once more in the embrace and reluctantly he released me.░ Somehow, the goodbyes were still awkward and I found myself more than a little empty headed when I closed the door behind me.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Maybe it's just dating jitters or maybe Var's little chat with me had more of an impact than I'd like to admit.░ Either way, better to support him through this. He'll deal with Var on his own terms and come out better for it.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>In the mean time, I had to consider what I was going to do with the rest of my evening.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>No one was home when I got there. Coby was likely still out partying it up.░ Which meant I was free to do what I wanted.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Awww, c'mon!░ First at the club and now this? I can only take so much teasing.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Well, you know the old joke about sadists and masochists kid?░ The masochist says, 'Fuck me, fuck me rough!' and the sadist says, 'No.'
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>My cheeks flushed again as Dustin stepped in close to me and ran his paw along my head.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Just imagine how pent up we'll be when we meet up next.░ I'll make you explode.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>I quivered under his grasp, my lips parting into a soft whine as he pulled me close to that firm body and bathed me in his scent.░ Shuddering, I barely noticed when he stepped back, arms crossed.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Now, head on home, enjoy those dreams about me and give me a call tommorow when you're ready to make 'em real.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>I nodded profusely, smiling at the thought before I showed myself out.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>In the cool night air, the anticipation just kept gnawing at me.░ The thought of feeling Dustin over me, him throwing me on the bed and having his way with me.░ I was giddy and walking awkward by the time I got home.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>It was silent when I got home. Coby was likely still out and the lights were all off. Sitting in the dark, I considered what I was going to do with the rest of my evening...
besides a cold shower.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Kid,░ I don't know if you ever had a bad breakup but it's rotten for the libido. I just need some time alone. Believe me, I'm just as frustrated as you are.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Dustin stepped up to me, placing a hand on my hip and leaning in to kiss me softly on the cheek.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I had fun tonight, %playername%. It ended with some shit I didn't intend but it's not going to be the last we see of each other.░ Tonight, I just need some space. Tomorrow, or whenever you're free, give me a call and we'll definately have a good time then.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>That smile seems tailor made to disarm me.░ I suppose if I waited this long, I can wait a little longer.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I'm holding you to that Dustin.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I'm sure it's not the only thing you'll be holding next time, kid.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>I blushed as his hand gave my backside a firm squeeze.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: For now, I'm ready to just flop into bed.░ Feels like the night's gone on forever.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>I was tempted to follow, slide on under the covers with him and see if I couldn't cajole a little fun out of him.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>...but that would be jeopardizing anything else that might come of this.░ For now, I just took my leave and walked out into the cool night air with my pants feeling a size too small.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>The walk home gave me time to cool down and think more about my situation.░ Sure, Var was going to be an ass about this,░ but I think what I've got with Dustin could go somewhere.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>For now, though, I had to think about what to do for the rest of my evening.░ With no one home and just me sleeping in my bed tonight, I just needed to fill the next few hours...
after a cold shower.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I couldn't leave well enough alone.░ Our first date didn't go well and I needed to find out why.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I hadn't yet deleted Dustin from my phone so I figured I'd just call and see what happened.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>*Ring*... ░*Ring*...░ *Ring*...
*Beep-Beep Beep*
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>He didn't pick up. ░ Maybe he didn't hear. I'll try again.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>*Ring*...░ *Ring*... *Ri-*
*Click*
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: ...Kid, why are you calling me?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>I froze for a moment.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Look, I made myself clear at the theater.░ There's nothin' there, kid. Start looking elsewhere.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Wait!░ I... I don't understand what went wrong. Maybe, I'm just sucky at this dating thing but, I think I deserve something more than watching you walk away.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Maybe this really was a bad idea.░ He seems upset that I called him back after our date.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
Nothin' to say?░ Not surprising.
*Click*
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>It keeps ringing but he doesn't pick up.░ He probably blocked my number. Guess he really didn't want to talk to me anymore...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>He hung up on me!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Oh yeah?░ Like what, kid?
Events.Title: Dustin

Choices.Text: You don't get to talk to me like that.

Events.Text: Like what went wrong?░ Honestly. Explain like I'm an idiot.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Hey!░ You're the one who brushed me off and walked out the door. You don't get to act like I don't matter.░ That really hurt!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: How about the fact that I take you to a movie, treat you as nice as possible and you shit all over my movie choice just because it doesn't have enough CGI?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: How about the fact that you say you like the movie but wouldn't even bother when those kids kept interrupting and being little fucks?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: ... part of why I like those old movies is because I love to talk about them.░ They had a whole different approach to characterization and flow.░ You didn't seem interested in anything but sitting there quietly.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Like I said, kid, there just wasn't anything there. I wasted plenty of time on dating Var and I'm done being someone's therapist while they work through their own shit.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>I suppose I did ask for honesty.░ Seems like it was a bit more than just ordering the wrong thing.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Okay, fair enough.░ Maybe the date wasn't exactly what you or I had intended, but you didn't exactly leave me much room to talk either.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Wait a sec. Really? THAT'S the reason you just walked away?░ Geeze, you're more shallow than I thought.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
Okay...░
you've got a point, kid.░ Guess I've gotten a bit too blunt when getting to know people. Blame a string of bad friend choices in my past.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I could be wrong, kid, but I'm pretty sure YOU called me,░ and you did ask me to be honest.░ If you just called to fuck with me, I'm hanging up now.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I know about your baggage, Dustin. It comes up fairly often in these conversations.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Look, I screwed up but you didn't let me know, you just walked away.░ How's that fair? I'm the one who has been out of the loop the longest after all.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Heh... Okay, okay,░ I admit,░ I was too hard on you, kid. I get that. I can give it another shot if you're willing.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: See, it's shit like that... I mean, what's your deal? You call me to complain about not getting a fair shake and then dump on my stuff?░ Do you just like fucking with people?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: That's not what I meant, Dustin!░ It's tough being compared with all your previous relationships!░ I want to be judged on who I am and not how I rank against others.░ You treat everything I do like it's your ex's early warning sign,░ what if it's just me trying to get comfortable?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Yeah.░ Particularly guys who walk out on me in the middle of  a date for no reason.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>*Click*
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>Clearly, he REALLY didn't like that.░ I don't think I'm going to get another chance with him.
I should just delete his number...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>The silence on the line made me worry he'd hung up on me.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
...you're right.░
Var was a rollercoaster and I'm just way too tired of that to go through it again.░ It was a shitty thing to do,░ I just saw the flags, you know?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Yup. It was shitty.░ I know it was just a first date but that was a big step for me. To just have you walk out, particularly when you were so eager at the club...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I'm not saying it didn't hurt, but I get where you're coming from at least.░ You don't want to burn yourself again.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Let's give it another shot.░ Something simple and relaxing. Take a little time to get to know each other better.░ Sound fair?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Sorry, I can't if we're going to keep having this conversation.░ It was hard enough putting myself out there...░ maybe we're just not meant for this.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>A soft sigh rolled through the speaker.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
You had to speak your piece, and I respect that.░ Hope you've got better luck in the future, kid.░ Take care. I mean it.
<i>*Click*
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text:
<i>As the line went dead, I could feel a tremble in my hand.░ Might have been the hardest thing to do but I don't want someone who would walk out so casually.
I'd better delete his number before I rethink this.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I'd like that.░ This has been a hard thing to do, harder than finding a job it feels like... ░but I think it could be worth the effort.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I'm thinking so too, kid.░ Gimmie a bit to come down from this and we'll talk more about what to do.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Alright Dustin. Take care.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
You too, kid.
<i>*Click*
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>I felt a tremble as I hung up the phone.░ It was rough, calling and confronting the issue but I feel like he's worth it.░ Does make me curious as to what he might have planned.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I wouldn't have called you if I wasn't.░ Just, give me a chance this time. The movie was a 'you' thing, I'd like to try an 'us' thing.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I get that.░ Tell you what, I'll set up something simple and relaxing.░ Give me a call when you're ready and we'll both give this another shot.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text:
Sounds good...░
Thanks, Dustin.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Kid, thank you for being willing to call me on my shit.░ There's hope for you yet. I'll catch you later.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>I stared at my phone for a moment after the call ended and took a deep breath.░ It's been rough so far, hopefully he has something fun planned.
Events.Title: %playername%

Choices.Text: Wait, I didn't mean it like that!

Events.Text:
No.░ I mean, you didn't even give any thought to my end of this?░ I know you've got Var and other stuff going on but I'm a person too.░
I didn't deserve to be dumped because you can't take the time to get to know me better.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Then you should probably hang up now, asshole. Because that was some middle school level shit you put me through.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I could hear the low rumble of a growl through the phone. He's pissed, I'm pissed and I'm not sure how this is going to end.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: So, what,░ I'm an ass because I didn't want to wind up in another dead end relationship?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text:
No.░
You're an ass because you didn't expect this to be anything but a dead end relationship.░ There's two of us here, you know.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: You little prick. Where do you get off telling me ANYTHING!░ You had your chance and now you just wanna get back at me 'cause I didn't pound your ass back in the club?░ THAT is some middle school bullshit!
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Shit.░ Fucking shit.░ Hah, I guess we're both rustier than we thought at dating. Fuck, I didn't even give you much of a chance, did I?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>By now, my hand was trembling and breath was coming in short bursts.░ He hurt me and now gives me shit for calling him on it?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: No, you didn't. We did your thing and when it didn't go perfect, you bailed. It's a shitty thing to do no matter how you look at it.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: You can't fucking see beyond your own goddamn problems and you don't give even half a fuck about me, do you?░ Then you can go fuck off yourself!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I threw my phone across the room, tears welling in my eyes.░ Wasn't the most auspicious start to my dating life but I'm pretty sure it's over now.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>My thumb fell to the button and the call ended. I didn't need this, particularly not from a guy like him.░ Not the best way to reenter the dating scene but it's over now.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Tears were rolling down my cheeks in waves and my voice started to crack.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: It hurts! Do you know how hard it is to be alone for so long and then when you try to open yourself up to a guy you met... just to have him walk away like you were nothing? Do you? Do you know that feeling? I know I'm just a 'kid' to you, but I was trying Dustin...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Only his breathing, slow and labored, clued me that he was still there. My phone was wet against my cheek and my eyes felt like they were on fire.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I'm... I'm sorry, %playername%.░ Jeeze. I really didn't think about you, just about avoiding another dead end relationship.░ I'm the biggest asshole in the world right now.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>It was hard enough to keep from openly sobbing, I just kept my mouth shut and let him talk.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: You're damn right you are.░ I didn't expect fireworks or anything... but I did want some consideration. I don't think that was much to ask.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
It's not.░ I'm sorry, %playername%.
Look, I... if you want to give this another try, I'm game.░ That said, I wouldn't fault you for deleting my number and never seeing me again.░ It's your choice. You deserve that.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I can't do it Dustin.░ Not if it means going through this again. I'm sorry.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Don't be.░ We've both got our stuff and I should apologize about mine getting in the way.░ You deserve better than that. Take care kid.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>The line went quiet and I felt the trembling begin to slow. Maybe sleep or a distraction... just, I don't think I should call him again.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Maybe it was worth another shot. Couldn't be any worse than how I feel now.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Alright.░ I'll give it a chance.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: ...Thanks, kid.░ I've got an idea for something relaxing, no pressure or expectations. Just time to get to know each other.░ Give me a call when you feel up to it.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>We hurried our goodbyes as I was all too eager to get a little silence to collect myself.░ I hope I wasn't making a mistake.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: More than fair.░ Guess I was too far up my own ass at the time as well.░ Maybe a getaway would be better. Time to just get to know each other better.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I'm not calling to recover anything. I just had to say my peace.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Harsh... but fair.░ Alright kid, sorry it wound up being a shitty time for you. Take care, alright?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Hanging up the call left me feeling empty but complete. It wasn't a good ending but it wasn't the worst either.░ Maybe I'd have better luck with someone else.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: That... I think I'd like that.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Think it over.░ I don't want to wind up with another night like the movies.░ Just give me a call when you're ready and we'll get together, alright?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Alright. I'll call you soon.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Take care, %playername%.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Maybe it was opening myself up for more hurt, but there was a certain desire to take the chance if it could mean something better.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: ...░Okay, maybe it was a little abrupt but you weren't having a good time and I wasn't having a good time. It wasn't worth prolonging the agony, kid.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: There you go again, just dismissing me. What the hell is your problem?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Kid, I'm not in this to have another failed relationship. Yeah, I should've said more but... jeeze, why are you dragging this out?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Because I deserve better than to have you throw me away like a piece of trash.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Oh? So you want an apology? Then I'm sorry you had a rotten time. There ya go. Enough closure for ya, kid?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Where do you even get off with this?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I've been through this song and dance way more times than I care to admit.░ We're not right for each other and I was willing to take the adult way out and just end it.░ Instead,░ you drag it out because of some desire for somethin'...
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: That's it? You guess it didn't work and cut your losses?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: You got somethin' more, kid?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>My finger slammed into the end call button. What kind of narcissistic asshole was that guy?░ I'm just glad I got out of it as quick as I did.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I've got plenty more! What kind of guy just dumps someone at the front of a theater?░ Not even counting the embarassment, you just abruptly leave me in a lurch like I was an <i>inconvenience?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Because despite what may have happened on our date, I don't want to give up.░ I'm not in this for petty crap, I like you. I liked your confidence at the club and getting to know a bit about you. I think that's worth it.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: You like me? Haha,░ what is this, high school?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: No. It's someone being honest with you for once. I like you,░ Dustin.░ It may not have worked out this time but I want to try again.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>The pause on the other end drew out for longer than I was comfortable with. Still, I wanted to see this through.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: And if it blows up again?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: It won't. I'll make sure of that. I think it's worth the risk or I wouldn't have called.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Then at least I know we won't work out and I'm not sitting here wondering what I did wrong after you just showed me the door and shut me down.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Heh. You've got quite a bit more confidence than I expected, %playername%. Alright,░ we'll do something a little more basic, maybe. See how it goes. Gimmie a call later on and we'll chat more.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>We said our goodbyes and I set my phone down. Maybe it wasn't going to work out but I'd rather know for sure.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Look, I've done this before and it's been always ended shitty...░ Heh... Okay, kid, I got nothing. I left because I didn't want to go through a failed relationship again.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: And that justifies walking out on me?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I met Var. I can't blame you for being skittish but that's no excuse.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
In the heat of the moment, yes.░ When you call me back afterward and point it out, no.
It was an asshole thing to do.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: You're right. Been carrying around lots of excuses lately. Sorry to leave you on the short end of one.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: So, where does that leave us then?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: That's the question.░ I want to make up for what I did but that's up to you. Wouldn't be fair to drag you along with me just because I don't have Var anymore.
Events.Title: Dustin

Choices.Text: Sounds like you've still got a boyfriend.

Events.Text: I'm game if you are. Just, don't walk out again. We can talk this stuff out.

Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
I get it.░
Hurts, but I get it.░ Maybe I'll see you at the cafe after I get Var out of my system. Take care, %playername%.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>As the line went quiet, I set the phone down and let out a long sigh. Didn't expect dating to be so hard, I guess.░ Maybe I'd have better luck with someone else...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Fair enough.░ Let's take some time to chill first. Give me a call when you want to get together next and we'll take it slow.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>We both said our goodbyes and I felt myself untense. I never knew so much could go wrong in a date.░ This is going to be harder than I thought.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I didn't even think about you or what you were feeling and... shit, I'm not great at this part.░ I've been too busy licking my own wounds to notice yours.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I don't deserve a second chance but, I think you deserve a real date.░ It's completely up to you and I can't blame you if you want to tell me to fuck off.

Events.Text: Wait...░ He blocked my number?!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>*Ring*...░ *Ring*...
*Click*

Events.Text: Hey,░ %playername%! Sorry, was a little busy.

Events.Text: <i>It didn't take much for me to realize what was keeping him busy when I heard Vareoth's voice over the phone.

Events.Text: <i>-hat your... toy, Dust...?

Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Sorry about that. Var's being worse than usual about all this.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: At this point I think I seriously need a vacation.░ Thinking you might want to come along too.
