Events.Text: There's this great little inlet not too far outside of town. It's more secluded than the main drag and less likely to be choked with tourists.░ Thought we could spend some time there.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I could use the time away from the house and the job hunt myself.░ Relaxing on a beach and soaking up sun sounds pretty good right now.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I don't know. Maybe another time...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Heh... I get it.░ Having second thoughts after I left you in the lurch?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: No. That's not it, Dustin.░ Just got other things on my plate at the moment. As soon as I'm free, I'll call you back.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>There was a brief pause on his end.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Alright.░ I'll keep the phone handy. Just let me know, alright?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>After the phone went silent, I began to wonder if I made the right choice.░ Maybe things had been a little uncertain with Dustin but leaving him hanging wasn't fair either, was it?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I won't lie. It still hurts.░ Mostly, I just don't want to be taken out on a pity date.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Nothing pitiable about it.░ Just some time to relax and get to know each other better. Give this a fair shot, far away from both of our problems.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I'm glad to hear it.░ I know last time... didn't go so well. I'm really looking forward to giving this another shot.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Thanks.░ I appreciate that.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Hey. I'm just glad we got back to speaking terms.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: It's a date then!░ Head over to my place when you get a chance and buzz me when you're there.░ Everything's good to go.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I'll see you then!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Sadly he didn't get much of a goodbye before I heard Var's voice echoing in the background.░ I swear that bird makes claws on a chalkboard sound pleasant.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Regardless, I needed to get my things together and head over.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>He sounded sincere.░ It was rough, what we went through after the theater, but maybe he really did want to make good.
Events.Title: %playername%

Choices.Text: Alright. I'll give it a shot.

Events.Text: Let me think about it, Dustin. I just need a little more time.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Alright. I suppose I should give you the benefit of the doubt too.░ I'm game.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
Fair enough. I know I've got my hands full here at the moment. Just give me a call back if you change your mind, kid.
<i>*Click*
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Maybe I should have given him another shot.░ I was probably just using being busy as an excuse.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I tapped Dustin's contact on my phone and waited for a moment. I still expected to hear Var in the background but when he picked up, there was nothing else.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Hey! Thanks for callin' back. Sorry about earlier, Var's being even more of a brat than usual.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I've had a couple of rough dates in my past. I know how messy breakups can be.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Does he just not have anything else to do with his life but harass you?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Yeah. Var's never been one for taking this kinda stuff easily.░ Still it's no reason to mess up what we might have.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Hah, that's a good question. Seems like I've become his pet harrassment project lately.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>I was a little surprised he wasn't more defensive about Var.░ Maybe something's changed?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Hopefully you're calling back because you changed your mind?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I did.░ I needed some time to think about it but I think a trip to the beach sounds great!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Dustin, I know this has been a  roller coaster but I don't think I can handle this anymore.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>There was silence on his end for a long time,
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I think, this was a mistake.░ You've got Var to deal with and I'm just not ready for that.░ It doesn't seem like you're ready to date and competing with him is killing me.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: So that's it, then?░ We bounce around a couple of times and you get cold feet?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I'm just not ready...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Bullshit.░ Bad enough that I'm getting this kind of crap from Var...░ Look, just don't call me again, kid.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text:
<i>The line went dead. No warning, no nothing.░ I think I need some work on my breakup technique as well...
Guess I wont be needing his number anymore
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Glad to hear it!░ I've got my things ready and Var's long gone. We can meet up here and head out, if that works for you.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Sounds good!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Alright! I'll see ya in a little bit!
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>After I put my phone away, I realized I didn't have anything ready for a trip to the beach!░ I'd better hurry up and fix that!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: The crap with Var is half of-
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: *Click*
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Wait, is Var still living with you? I thought he was already on his way out...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: It's... complicated.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Uncomplicated version?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: The short version is that he's bounced over three couches, including his dad's,░ and now he's back here. It's temporary and he's on the couch.░ It's gonna be the longest week of my damn life,░ so save me from sitting here between his boxes and let me take you out somewhere.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>A quick side trip later and I headed out of the suburbs and into the city.░ True, half the city was a beach but if Dustin knew a place that was more secluded, that would certainly be a treat.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>The parking lot below Dustin's apartment complex was packed solid with cars.░ It'd be impossible to figure out which one was his!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Fortunately, Dustin strolled out of the elevator and waved me down.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Hey %playername%! Glad you could make it!
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>He walked up to me and gave me a brief hug, a smile beaming on his face.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: It's good to see ya again.░ I'm really looking forward to relaxing and getting to know you a little better.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>His smile turned a little predatory as he glanced around the parking lot.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: But first, I've got a little game I wanted to play.░ It's called, Guess Which One Is Mine!
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>My brow furrowed and he laughed.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: It's just for fun!░ Which car do you think is mine?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Kind of an odd game I suppose, but I can humor him.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>There was a cherry red sports car in immacuate condition towards the front of the garage.░ Something about it suggested 'Dustin'.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: That one?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Haha, I wish. You've got great taste in cars though!
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Tucked into a corner was a sleek, black luxury car with leather seats and slightly tinted windows.░ Maybe that's his car?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: How about that one?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Heh, only if Var's dad was buying me a car. Even then, I'd be afraid to drive it!
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>A beefy hunter green SUV was wedged in between two smaller cars but it seemed to dominate its spot.░ That screams 'Dustin' to me.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Could it be that one?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Heh. Not really my scene, kid. Chugs gas and generally looks obnoxious out on the road.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Inconspiciously tucked away towards the back of the lot was an older, powder blue pickup truck.░ It had seen better days but there was something comfortable about it. It looked like something I could see him in.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Maybe that one?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Good call, kid!░ That's Old Reliable. The first car I ever bought with my own cash after I started at the cafe.░ Maybe you know me better than I thought!
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Overshadowed by a massive SUV was a smaller commuter car. It was a deep navy blue and while it didn't stand out, it looked very comfortable and zippy. I think that's his car.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Possibly that one?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Cheap and sensible, huh? Haha, can't blame you, I suppose, but nope. That's not it.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: There's my baby right there!
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>He motioned to a pickup truck in the back of the lot.░ It was powder blue and looked like it had seen better days. Not quite what I was expecting.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Huh. Would have never guessed!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: And that's why we're gettin' to know each other better, kid!░ That pickup means the world to me. It was my first car and the first real thing I had that I could call my own.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: That truck let me be independent,░ for once. Helped me to make my own way.░ It's full of memories.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>He must really like that pickup, considering the amount of work he's likely put into it.░ Still, it wasn't rickety or anything░: just well loved and long lived.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Toss your stuff in the back, kid.░ We should get going! It's a bit of a drive out to the beach.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>I nodded and set my bag in the bed of the truck.░ I'd noticed he'd already loaded in a couple of folding chairs and a cooler as well as his own things.░ A black speedo peeked out of the rucksack he'd tossed next to the cooler.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Despite wanting to take the time to get to know him better, I couldn't help but blush at the idea of him in those.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Hop in, kid!
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>The heavy doors of the truck slammed shut as the engine reluctantly revved to life. After a moment's hesitation,░ a cough of the engine,░ the truck lurched to life and we were on our way!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Despite a questionable, roaring start, the truck's ride was remarkably smooth.░ Dustin and I chatted about the little things, weather and the like, before settled into a more serious tone.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I just wanna say that, after the theater...░ Thanks for calling me back, getting me to try this again.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I wanted to thank you for giving me a reason to get Var out the door quickly.░ I think I need this getaway badly.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I thought we deserved another shot.░ Took me some time to get there, but I think it's worth it.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I know you dated that guy, but he gets on my nerves.░ I'm surprised he doesn't drive you crazy more often.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Saying it's complicated would be a understatement.░ <i>Haha...
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I do too.░ Not many people would have gotten back in touch with me after a date like that. Fewer still would wanna try again.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text:
...░
Vareoth was special to you, wasn't he?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Was...░ Now? Heh...░ weird to think about it that way. We've been on and off again more than a light switch but somehow I always wound up right back where I started.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: You mean with him?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: More than that.░ Everything seemed to just settle back into the same routine.░ Work, dates, bills... even old Betsy here would seem to wind up with the same issues again.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Sounds like you were stuck in a rut or something. I've had a little of that lately myself.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: You named your truck Betsy?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Hahaha...░ Yup, first girl I dated in high school. Awkward, cumbersome, needed a bunch of maintenance... just seemed like the name was a perfect fit.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Never quite felt that simple. You can bust yourself out of a rut... ░This, though,░ kinda felt like the world was settling around me and I didn't mind. Bothers me whenever I think about it, though.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Takes a certain kind of person to name their car, you know.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Still, yeah... Var was important to me.░ Now?░ I don't even know. I certainly don't think I'm that important to him.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>I got quiet for a moment. It never really occurred to me that Dustin would be aware of Vareoth's manipulations, since it seemed he just went along with them.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>It made me think back to before I went to Amorous,░ that strange sort of hazy feeling I had at the start.░ I was in a rut, frustrated with the job hunt and going nowhere but I still came back.░ I still turned to Coby drag me out of it.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Looks like we're in luck! No one else is out here and there's plenty of parking right by the beach!
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>We pulled to a stop and got out, grabbing our things from the bed of the truck and hiking down the narrow stairs to the sand below.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I suppose it didn't matter what we had going on before now. The only thing that was worth thinking about was enjoying the sun, the surf and the company.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Dustin wasn't kidding about the beach being secluded.░ Sheer cliffs of sandstone blocked off access from the main road and the inlet looked like it had been carved out from an underground spout.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Still, the sun was in just the right position to flood the tiny beach and the waves were softly lapping at the shore. It was picturesque!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Dustin started by folding out the chairs and tossing down a blanket over the sand.░ Settling the cooler in the middle, he set up a small beach umbrella towards the back before smiling over at me.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: There we go. Our own little slice of heaven.░ Speaking of which...
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Dustin uncerimoniously shucked off his shirt, tossing it over the back of one of the chairs.░ After a short stretch, he settled in onto the blanket, leaving his chest exposed to the sun.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Ahhh, man, I live for this. Nothing like the feel of warm sun on your fur.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Heh! You are such a cat stereotype, curling up in a sunbeam the first chance you get!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: No use denying my heritage!░ Prrr-rrr. It's sooo good.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Hey now, you're not the only one who likes to sunbathe!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I slipped out of my shirt and tossed it on the seat of my chair before joining Dustin in his hedonism.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Yet another reason I like having you around, kid!
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Sorry, I burn pretty easily. That said, I enjoy the view.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: You mean me or the ocean?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Both of course!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Me and the ocean appreciate the compliment.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: You, of course!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Dustin smiled slyly and adjusted his position to best emphasize his broad, tawny chest and smouldering green eyes,
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Guess you've got better taste than I thought, kid.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Oh, I just mean the ocean. It's so blue and big and wet.░ How can you not be astounded?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Dustin gave me a playful glower before returning to sucking up the sunlight.░ I chuckled to myself and relaxed under the umbrella.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: So, how did you find this place?░ A secluded little cove like this should be a hot spot for everyone looking for a little privacy.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Dustin squinted a little into the bright blue sky before rolling onto one side to face me.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: It was early on with Var.░ Back when he just wanted to get away from everything. I was his major form of escape at the time.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Escape from what?░ Seems like he was perfectly happy with where he was when I talked to him.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Used to be, he wasn't that into money and getting stuff.░ I figure it was just his teenage rebellious phase spilling over.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: One day, he shows up at my place in the middle of the night with a beach towel and a cooler of beer.░ Said his dad tried to set him up with someone from work for a date or something.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: So we hopped into my truck and just drove. He tossed back a couple of beers and snuggled up to me.░ When we passed near here, he saw the moonlight off the waves and said we should stop.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: And... hah, well,░ obviously we did.░ Stayed out until 1am just listening to the waves and drinking.░ We both didn't want to risk driving back, so we just slept on the beach and drove home after sunrise.░ Man, his dad was pissed.
Events.Title: Dustin

Choices.Text: Doesn't sound like the Var I saw.

Events.Text: That doesn't sound at all like the arrogant parrot I met at your place.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: People change.░ I see it enough at work, I should have seen it at home too.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: ...that's why he's important to you?░ Why you've been putting up with him and why he still lingers around.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
It's like I said on the drive over, it was a comfortable sort of routine.░ Easy to fall back into regardless of what happened.
But...
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Am I always going to be competing with that memory?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Gettin' kinda heavy for a relaxing beach trip, aren't you kid?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: To be honest,░ I think we're both competing with that memory.░ Me,░ seeing what Var is now,░ and you... coming in at the end of the trainwreck that was.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: But I'll tell you, it's different now.░ That routine isn't comfortable anymore and I'm ready for a new one.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>The waves washed away everything else for the moment. I knew my uncertanty was going to linger. Knowing just how far back Var went, I couldn't help but remember his taunts.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>He'll dump you by the curb...
Events.Title: Vareoth

Events.Text: <i>For the moment,░ no matter what either of us went through,░ he was willing to share this.░ Laying in the sun,░ near the surf,░ he wanted to take the time to be here with me. That's worth something.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: You got quiet there for a second, kid. Something on your mind?
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Part of me wanted to talk to him about all this but at the same time, seeing that handsome lion looking up at me...░ I didn't want to ruin the moment.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: No, nothing important. Just kinda lost in the moment.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Just thinking about us.░ This whole... situation and where it all might end up.░ I forgot how complicated dating can be sometimes. Heck, I forgot how complicated people can be...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I know something that'll pull you back to the present.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: It's not easy, sure,░ but nothing worth doing is.░ Well, except for one thing...
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>To my surprise, Dustin stood up from his blanket and moved over next to me.░ His paw ran softly along my shoulder and down the back of my neck as he leaned in close.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Gently, his lips brushed my own as he pulled me towards him for a long, luxurious kiss.░ I could feel his strength wrapped around me and the tickle of his rough tongue against mine.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>There was a tenderness, a warmth that radiated through the kiss.░ The sunbathing had left his fur achingly hot and the rolling warmth of the breath left me slumped into his arms.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Then the cool ocean breeze passed over my lips, the shock of seperation from him pulling me back from my haze. HIs paw stroked my neck softly, his smile beaming down over me.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: That's something Vareoth and I never did here.░ A new memory that I'm enjoying greatly.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>I felt a chill rise from around me. Maybe it was the ocean or maybe it was my nerves but I pushed forward into that thick-furred warmth and buried my face in his mane.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I take it that it was a good memory for you too, then!
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>I mumbled and nodded, surrounded by silken fur that trapped me in waves of warmth. His scent filled my nostrils and left me dizzy.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Pulling back just a little, I grinned fiendishly up at him.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: For some parts of me, an extremely good memory!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>He continued to stroke my head and neck softly, stretching out to catch a few sunbeams more.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Haha,░ straight to the point again, huh?░ Don't mind that.░ Well, as much as we might enjoy going further...░ getting sand in your skivvies makes it much less fun.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Much as I wanted to disgree, the idea did sound rather... chafe-y.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Dustin snuggled up next to me, watching the waves roll down along the shore and keeping an arm around my shoulders.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>It was a vastly different date, and a different Dustin than I had first met.░ I felt more comfortable with him, less like I was just another one night stand.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>We stayed out until just before sunset, the chill eventually getting too much for me and Dustin to bare.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: We should get going. It's only going to get colder at this point.
Events.Title: Dustin

Choices.Text: Awww... You put your shirt on!

Events.Text: Awww... why'd you have to put your shirt back on?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Hah,░ because,░ despite my furry hide,░ I was getting a chill.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Though I know you feel cheated at not getting to stare at my chest anymore.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Everything about this date has been so relaxing and perfect. I never wanted to leave!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Can't we just stay here?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I'd love to just stay here, set up a little hut? If you're willing to take up spearfishing and wear nothing but a loincloth.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: ...I'm not seeing a downside here.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Dustin grinned and tossed one of the beach towels at me.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
Well I've got to go to work in the morning and I'm your ride...
It gets cold her, %playername%, and as much as I really enjoyed getting things off our chest,░ I didn't bring stuff to set up a fire for the night.░
I promise it won't be the last time we come here.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I suppose I am getting a little chilly.░ Though I hate to leave such a beautiful spot.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
I promise, this won't be the last time we come here.
And next time,░ maybe I wont have work in the morning.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>Begrudingly, I gathered up my things and the cooler as Dustin grabbed the blanket and umbrella.░ The warmth came back to use as we moved up the trail towards the truck and I felt a little of that hazy, dreamy-feeling from his embrace.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Powering through, I tossed my bundle into the back of the truck and hopped back inside.░ Once the doors shut, the truck roared to life immediately. My surprise was echoed on Dustin's face.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Guess Betsy likes you too!
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>We both chuckled as he pulled smoothly out of the parking lot and back onto the main road.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>The trip back was much lighter than the one over. I was still riding on the high of that kiss and Dustin's paw had found its way to mine, squeezing it firmly.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>We talked for a while longer, since he insisted on dropping me by my house instead of making me walk home.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: ...I wanna see where you live anyway,░ just in case I want to drop by and say hi.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>As we pulled up to the house, Dustin parked and the two of us walked to the front door.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Nice place your parents have.░ Cozy,░ but spacious.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Not quite spacious enough that I get my own room, but my brother and I get along well enough.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Heh...░ Well,░ I suppose this is where I should say good night. Don't want your dad to come out and kick my ass for bringing you home after curfew.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: I'm an adult, Dustin. Don't be a dick.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>He grinned at me and leaned in to kiss me on the cheek.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Gimmie a call soon, kid.░ I don't like to be kept waiting for long.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>As I waved goodbye, I could feel eyes on me. Turning around, I drew in a deep sigh when I saw who it was.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Sooo...░ Who was that?
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text: <i>Suddenly I feel like it's going to be a long night...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: He keeps coming up, regardless.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I hadn't seen Dustin for a couple of days.░ Not a major issue usually but I figured I should give him a call and see what was up.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>*Ring*...░ *Ring*...░

Events.Text: <i>We spent a few moments trying to clean up, throwing on sandy clothes and making certain no one saw us.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Fortunately, it remained our little secret and by the time the sun had dipped into the horizon, we were packed up and ready to go.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>There isn't much you can say after a night like that. I felt closer than ever to Dustin but more importantly, he was willing to get close to me.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I couldn't let his hand go the whole ride home and he didn't try to stop me.░ It didn't matter if we'd ruined his backseats, or that it smelled like a beachfront brothel.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>All that mattered, for now, was the ride home and the promise of what might be tomorrow.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>We got back to my place without incident.░ My dad was just getting ready for bed and only gave me a passing glower before disappearing into his room.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I guess... this is good night, %playername%.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: Guess so.░ I'll call you again, sometime?
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>He leaned forward and kissed me gently on the cheek.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Any time, kid. Any time at all.
Events.Title: Dustin

Events.Text: <i>I returned his parting kiss, squeezing his hands softly before letting go and watching him walk out the door.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>It might not wind up perfect in the end...░ but I'll take what I've got right now over that chance.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Finished
